prompts.template:
Read the Python script at {script_path} and generate an mcp_tools.json tool entry.

Category for namespacing: {category}

Extract from the script:
- Tool name (from filename, without .py)
- Description (from module docstring)
- Parameters (from argparse arguments)

Output a JSON object in this format:
{{
  "name": "tool_name",
  "script": "filename.py",
  "description": "What it does.",
  "params": [
    {{"name": "param_name", "flag": "--param-name", "required": true, "description": "..." }}
  ]
}}
